# ADR-0001: Adopt the Irminsul doc system

## Status

Accepted, {{ today }}.

## Context

Documentation rots when the right place to write something isn't obvious and when CI doesn't enforce structural rules. Without enforcement, things drift.

## Decision

Adopt Irminsul as the canonical doc system for {{ project_name }}. CI runs `irminsul check --scope=hard` on every PR.

## Alternatives considered

- **README.md alone** — fine until it isn't. Doesn't scale past one or two contributors.
- **Confluence / Notion** — separate repo, separate workflow. Drifts from code within weeks.

## Consequences

- Every PR that adds source code without doc updates gets flagged.
- New contributors have an obvious place to put each kind of writing.
- Schema definitions belong in `40-reference/` and are regenerated; they cannot live in component docs.
